00:01:52.477 --> 00:01:54.310
JACQUELINE NOVOGRATZ:
Probably the biggest--

00:01:54.310 --> 00:01:57.130
when we started Acumen,
it was clear to us

00:01:57.130 --> 00:01:59.260
that markets alone
were not going

00:01:59.260 --> 00:02:00.790
to solve the
problems of poverty,

00:02:00.790 --> 00:02:03.515
nor was charity by itself.

00:02:03.515 --> 00:02:05.890
And so we had this idea, as
you know, of patient capital.

00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:08.020
That we would take
philanthropy and we

00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:09.850
would invest in
intrepid entrepreneurs

00:02:09.850 --> 00:02:13.870
for the long term, 10, 12
years to disrupt systems.

00:02:13.870 --> 00:02:18.940
And 16 years later,
often credited

00:02:18.940 --> 00:02:24.040
as being one of the pioneers
of the impact investing sector,

00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:27.310
I would say what
makes us still feel

00:02:27.310 --> 00:02:30.250
proudest is this recognition
that you can use capital

00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:33.190
as a means to solving problems.

00:02:33.190 --> 00:02:36.820
We get in trouble if we see
it as an end in and of itself.

00:02:36.820 --> 00:02:39.970
