invest, give these entrepreneurs

00:03:29.140 --> 00:03:33.650
the time to experiment,
to fail, to try again.

00:03:33.650 --> 00:03:36.910
And lo and behold, we have seen,
as you said, 200 million people

00:03:36.910 --> 00:03:40.360
get access to services
and new models for how

00:03:40.360 --> 00:03:44.240
we solve problems of
poverty for the world.

00:03:44.240 --> 00:03:47.980
PRASAD SETTY: And as you
think about then the learnings

00:03:47.980 --> 00:03:52.810
from this journey that
influence how you're are

00:03:52.810 --> 00:03:55.289
thinking about the future,
what stands out for you?

00:03:55.289 --> 00:03:56.830
JACQUELINE NOVOGRATZ:
So in many ways

00:03:56.830 --> 00:04:01.220
we grew up against the global
backdrop of the last 15,

00:04:01.220 --> 00:04:01.780
16 years.

00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:04.900
If you think about it, when
Acumen was started in 2001

00:04:04.900 --> 00:04:08.090
the world was a very
different place.

00:04:08.090 --> 00:04:12.520
Whether you're talking
about cell phone technology,

00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:17.079
post-9/11 versus pre-9/11
and the lack of trust around

00:04:17.079 --> 00:04:21.579
the world, the inequality that
we're seeing as well as real

00:04:21.579 --> 00:04:24.190
questions of capitalism
that are coming on.

00:04:24.190 --> 00:04:29.830
So in many ways Acumen has
moved from simply focusing

00:04:29.830 --> 00:04:31.630
on entrepreneurs that
are trying to solve

00:04:31.630 --> 00:04:33.500
specific problems
of poverty, Prasad,

00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:38.380
to where we fit into
building an ecosystem that

00:04:38.380 --> 00:04:42.340
can take on the issues
of capitalism, frankly.

00:04:42.340 --> 00:04:47.020
How do we create a more
inclusive capitalism?

00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:48.580
Not just Acumen,
but the world is

00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:50.890
starting to see that we
must move from shareholders

00:04:50.890 --> 00:04:52.140
to stakeholders.

00:04:52.140 --> 00:04:54.640
For us those stakeholders
have to include the poor

00:04:54.640 --> 00:04:56.710
and have to include
the environment.

00:04:56.710 --> 00:04:59.470
The world is seeing that we need
a long term, not a short term

00:04:59.470 --> 00:05:02.022
impact, which is something
that we have stood for.

00:05:02.022 --> 00:05:03.730
The world is seeing
that we have to start

00:05:03.730 --> 00:05:07.720
with purpose before profit
rather than just do good and do

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:08.710
well.

00:05:08.710 --> 00:05:11.710
And that we need
to define success

00:05:11.710 --> 00:05:15.010
more than how the rich fare
but how the poor and vulnerable

00:05:15.010 --> 00:05:16.210
are treated.

00:05:16.210 --> 00:05:20.230
And so I think that this
drive as we've seen the world

00:05:20.230 --> 00:05:23.950
move from interconnected
to interdependent

00:05:23.950 --> 00:05:27.370
allows Acumen to play a very
different role on the capital

00:05:27.370 --> 00:05:31.840
side as well as on the
kinds of entrepreneurs

00:05:31.840 --> 00:05:35.740
and the kinds of
businesses that will

00:05:35.740 --> 00:05:39.644
enable a more sustainable
world for all of us.

00:05:39.644 --> 00:05:41.560
PRASAD SETTY: You mentioned
quite a few things

00:05:41.560 --> 00:05:44.710
that I'd love for us to
