00:20:36.970 --> 00:20:40.750
At that time we also
were given amazing office

00:20:40.750 --> 00:20:44.000
space in New York City
that lasted nine years.

00:20:44.000 --> 00:20:46.630
And for that we are
eternally grateful.

00:20:46.630 --> 00:20:51.340
So many nonprofits have to sit
away at a cubbyhole somewhere.

00:20:51.340 --> 00:20:54.400
And having a great location
with Google right upstairs

00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:56.920
enabled a real relationship.

00:20:56.920 --> 00:21:01.960
And we have a huge debt
to many of the Googlers--

00:21:01.960 --> 00:21:04.690
Craig and Kirsten [INAUDIBLE]
who've become real partners

00:21:04.690 --> 00:21:09.610
to us, Doug Brody, others, you--

00:21:09.610 --> 00:21:14.590
that really supported us
in concrete as well as

00:21:14.590 --> 00:21:18.670
inspirational ways that you
probably don't even know.

00:21:18.670 --> 00:21:22.920
And then in 2010 Google
gave us $2 million

00:21:22.920 --> 00:21:29.920
in philanthropy to do this
early stage work in solar.

00:21:29.920 --> 00:21:32.890
At that point we
were taking big bets

00:21:32.890 --> 00:21:37.510
in off grid solar where very
little was actually known.

00:21:37.510 --> 00:21:40.660
There was no investment,
particularly in Africa.

00:21:40.660 --> 00:21:43.180
Most people relied
on kerosene, take

00:21:43.180 --> 00:21:45.580
buying little bits
of kerosene every day

00:21:45.580 --> 00:21:49.870
by which they would read at
night with a lot of smoke

00:21:49.870 --> 00:21:50.950
and cook.

00:21:50.950 --> 00:21:54.070
And trying to
convert people seemed

00:21:54.070 --> 00:21:55.750
like it should be easy, right?

00:21:55.750 --> 00:21:59.380
But the truth is, you have
no trust, you have no income,

00:21:59.380 --> 00:22:01.780
you have no financing mechanism.

00:22:01.780 --> 00:22:05.140
And you've never
really seen solar work.

00:22:05.140 --> 00:22:10.060
And it takes a long time
to go from a push market

00:22:10.060 --> 00:22:11.470
to a pull market.

00:22:11.470 --> 00:22:13.970
And over 10 years we
invested about $20 million

00:22:13.970 --> 00:22:17.320
of philanthropic capital
in these companies.

00:22:17.320 --> 00:22:20.030
That taught us how
people make decisions,

00:22:20.030 --> 00:22:22.120
how to market in a way
that people could hear.

00:22:22.120 --> 00:22:25.030
It gave time for mobile
banking to enable the financing

00:22:25.030 --> 00:22:25.570
mechanism.

00:22:25.570 --> 00:22:29.110
We built brand recognition,
particularly Delight.

00:22:29.110 --> 00:22:31.870
Googlers helped in
many different aspects

00:22:31.870 --> 00:22:33.670
of that building
of a value chain

00:22:33.670 --> 00:22:35.560
that had not existed before.

00:22:35.560 --> 00:22:38.470
So much so that we were able
to take the Google money,

00:22:38.470 --> 00:22:41.530
leverage it 10 times with
the $20 million invested,

00:22:41.530 --> 00:22:43.030
and now are raising
a $100 million

00:22:43.030 --> 00:22:47.680
for-profit initiative so that
we can prove to government

00:22:47.680 --> 00:22:50.620
that off-grid solar is faster,
cheaper, and more effective

00:22:50.620 --> 00:22:52.090
than extending the grid.

00:22:52.090 --> 00:22:57.160
It takes $1,500 to get one
household connected to a grid--

00:22:57.160 --> 00:22:59.770
and as they say,
nine years to never.

00:22:59.770 --> 00:23:03.190
And for $170 people can
buy a 10 watt system--

00:23:03.190 --> 00:23:05.790
three lights, a
radio, a flashlight,

00:23:05.790 --> 00:23:07.750
a cell phone charger--

00:23:07.750 --> 00:23:10.240
and their life changes
overnight because of what

00:23:10.240 --> 00:23:12.880
they have done themselves.

00:23:12.880 --> 00:23:15.190
That is where dignity
gets to start.

00:23:15.190 --> 00:23:17.200
And we think Africa
can leapfrog the grid

00:23:17.200 --> 00:23:22.504
just like it did with the cell
phones leapfrogging, landlines.

00:23:22.504 --> 00:23:23.920
Googlers helped
there financially.

00:23:23.920 --> 00:23:28.030
They helped in terms of
design, thinking about some

00:23:28.030 --> 00:23:30.970
of the technology here.

00:23:30.970 --> 00:23:35.860
When you go to the volunteer
work that you talked about,

00:23:35.860 --> 00:23:40.779
many of our companies have
tech platforms for the work

00:23:40.779 --> 00:23:41.320
that they do.

00:23:41.320 --> 00:23:44.860
Whether it's a bank
in rural Pakistan

00:23:44.860 --> 00:23:47.320
that has 500,000
farmers and is now

00:23:47.320 --> 00:23:50.440
converting to mobile
banking, or LaborNet

00:23:50.440 --> 00:23:54.370
which I was talking about
before, or Esoko, which

00:23:54.370 --> 00:23:56.450
is a platform for
smallholder farmers based

00:23:56.450 --> 00:24:00.310
out of Ghana and now
Kenya to give farmers

00:24:00.310 --> 00:24:02.680
market information,
Google helped actually

00:24:02.680 --> 00:24:07.750
take that platform and,
one, both proposed a million

00:24:07.750 --> 00:24:11.710
dollar grant which the company
got, as well as helped design

00:24:11.710 --> 00:24:16.750
a platform for mobile banking
and the distribution of

00:24:16.750 --> 00:24:17.800
implements.

